<p>To add this web app as a standalone application:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Click on the <strong>Settings</strong> menu (three dots) in the top-right corner of Microsoft Edge.</li>
  <li>Scroll down and select <strong>Apps</strong>.</li>
  <li>Click on <strong>Install this site as an app</strong>.</li>
  <li>Review the installation details and click <strong>Install</strong>.</li>
  <li>The Joy of Rails icon will now be added as a standalone application.</li>
</ol>

<p>Once installed, you can find the web application in your <strong>Start</strong> menu or on your desktop.</p>
<p>Note: The availability of this feature may depend on your version of Microsoft Edge.</p>
